Phillipo Mpango, who was tabling the 2019-2020 budget in parliament was applauded by legislators when he made the proposals that are likely to be unpopular with ordinary Tanzanians. When the budget is approved, locally manufactured wigs will pay a 10% tax, while imported ones will attract a 25% tax. East African finance ministers including from Uganda, Rwanda, Kenya and Tanzania presented their budgets for the next financial year on Thursday. Mpango said Tanzania’s overall spending will rise 2% to $14.43 billion in 2019/2020. East Africa’s third-largest economy is investing heavily in public infrastructure projects as it seeks to profit from its long coastline and upgrade its rickety railways and roads to serve the growing economies in east and central Africa.  --Africa News--